    <item>
      <title>01 - What is evidence? And, how can it inform policy?</title>
      <link>https://seramirezruiz.github.io/data-science-for-policymaking/material/day-4/1-evidence/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 27 May 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://seramirezruiz.github.io/data-science-for-policymaking/material/day-4/1-evidence/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;summary&#34;&gt;Summary&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this session, we discuss the nature and types of evidence, including anecdotal, qualitative, and quantitative insights. Participants will learn think about indicators of progress and measures of effectiveness in monitoring and evaluation (M&amp;amp;E).We will also cover the models under which research insights feed into policy recommendations.&lt;/p&gt;
