    <item>
      <title>04 - How to read an academic study?</title>
      <link>https://seramirezruiz.github.io/data-science-for-policymaking/material/day-4/4-read-articles/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 27 May 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://seramirezruiz.github.io/data-science-for-policymaking/material/day-4/4-read-articles/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;summary&#34;&gt;Summary&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this session, we guide participants through the process of reading and understanding academic articles. Key skills include identifying the main arguments, evaluating the methodology, and assessing the significance and relevance of the findings for policy and practice.&lt;/p&gt;
